main event: Two large silver objects were observed in the sky for approximately 15 minutes before fading out of sight.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 15 minutes and took place at 0310Z on July 29, 1955., Observers reported that the objects appeared to be moving southwest., The observers included MRS GRACE REECE and five other persons in the area., The report suggests that the objects were considered not to be balloons despite initial theories., The sighting does not have supporting photographic evidence.
witnesses: MRS GRACE REECE and five other persons
